column5: A shoot, time warp and brain fart at the same time, nice photos anyway, will pay more attention for next time.
Dang Brandon I also missed the post or I would have been all over it to help you out sorry man next time send me a PM and I will get to voting right away.

Hey Everybody,  As some of you know I spend most of my time down in the Photography area of OFC.  Posting photos on here has really helped me get where I am today with photography.  Feedback goes a long way.  If any of you are familiar with the photog section, you'll remember last month I travelled to Alaska to photograph Grizzly Bears.  When I got home I submitted one of the photos to a Contest.  I was notified this morning that my photo had been chosen by judges out of 1100 entries as a top 12 finalist and now it's up to the public to choose their favourite.  This is where I need your help.  If any of you have a moment to spare, please send a vote my way.  The voting page is located here: http://www.naturetrust.bc.ca/photocontest_voting.php  As I mentioned my photo is the one with the Grizzlies.....it also says "bbroderick" underneath.  Thanks in advance!!  Brandon Broderick

Just voted Brandon, some amazing pictures on there.  I just bought a E620 myself (with the 2 kits lens) ... should be picking it up today or tomorrow ... i can't wait. Hopefully I'll be able to contribute a bit to the photography section and also hope to get some feedback/tips from you pros .  Good luck on the contest!

Category winners get a photo album that holds 40 13x19" prints and a camera bag...worth about $150 in total and the grand prize winner gets a Nikon D90 Camera and 18-105mm lens I believe worth about $1500.  and frozen fire, make sure you've picked your favorite photo in each category. I just wanna take this time to say Thank You to everybody who took the time to vote and get others to vote for my Grizzly Bear Photo.  Unfortunately this was not my year to win.  If you're interested, the winning photos can be seen here  http://www.naturetrust.bc.ca/  Thanks again,  Brandon
